title: Kanye West presidential campaigns
added: [[Joe Rogan]], American comedian and podcaster, mentioned his plan to vote for Kanye West during a podcast with [[Alex Jones]], merely based on the merit that it was tradition for Rogan to vote for candidates that have appeared as guests on his show. Despite his comment, he revealed later to have actually voted for [[Jo Jorgensen]].

title: Kanye West presidential campaigns
deleted: In October 2019, West spoke out against abortion, stating "[[thou shalt not kill]]". He also alleged that the [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic Party]] was pushing black people to use [[levonorgestrel]], commonly known as Plan B, as a form of [[Voter suppression in the United States|voter suppression]]. West's comments were praised by [[Anti-abortion movement|anti-abortion]] organizations [[Live Action (organization)|Live Action]] and [[Students for Life of America|Students for Life]], and the conservative news website ''[[The Daily Wire]]''.<ref>{{Cite magazine|title=Kanye West Claimed Democrats Make Black People Kill Their Children |url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/zmj5b8/kanye-west-interview-big-boy-democrats-abortion-and-plan-b|first=Susan|last=Rinkunas |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191215155700/https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/zmj5b8/kanye-west-interview-big-boy-democrats-abortion-and-plan-b |archive-date=December 15, 2019|date=October 28, 2019|accessdate=July 5, 2020 |magazine=Vice}}</ref> In July 2020, West stated "I am pro-life because I'm following the word of the Bible" and expressed his belief that "[[Planned Parenthood]]s have been placed inside cities by [[White supremacy|white supremacists]] to do the Devil's work."<ref name="Forbes"/> Nia Martin-Robinson of Planned Parenthood criticized West's statements, asserting that "[a]ny insinuation that [[Black genocide#Abortion|abortion is Black genocide]] is offensive and infantilizing".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/life/2020/07/planned-parenthood-responds-to-kanye-west|title=Planned Parenthood Responds to Kanye West Claiming It Does the 'Devil's Work'|author=Joe Price|website=Complex|date=July 8, 2020|accessdate=July 8, 2020|archive-date=November 23, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201123224454/https://www.complex.com/life/2020/07/planned-parenthood-responds-to-kanye-west|url-status=live}}</ref>

At a July rally in South Carolina, West stated abortion should be legal because "the law is not by God anyway". However, he proposed giving every mother that does not abort their child a financial incentive, using "$1 million or something in that range" as an example. He did not disclose how he would pay for such incentives.<ref name="BBCRally"/>
